Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.71,0:14:11.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't think so.{ないと思うよ。\Nえっ？}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.82,0:14:14.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the blood hadn't dried when\Nthe wallet and change were taken,{If the wallet and pocket change were taken before the blood had time to dry, / 血が乾いてから\N小銭や財布を取らないと→}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.56,0:14:18.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then this bloody character wouldn't have been so clearly defined.{then this character written in blood wouldn't have been as [sharply] recognizable as it is. / こんなくっきりした血文字は\N残らないからねぇ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.50,0:14:21.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then it actually {\i1}was{\i0} a theft case.{Then... that matches up with [this being] a theft case after all. / ゃあ　やっぱり窃盗事件で\N合ってたんだね。}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.74,0:14:23.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.{（世良）ああ！}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.71,0:14:28.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Though I'm surprised you figured it out, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!{However, I wouldn't have realized it if it wasn't for [you,] Conan-kun! / でも　コナン君\Nよく気がついたな！}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.84,0:14:33.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-It wasn't me who figured it out, but Shin'ichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-niichan{\r}.{I-I didn't realize anything, Shin'ichi-niichan did. / き　気づいたのは　僕じゃなくて\N新一兄ちゃんだよ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.12,0:14:35.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What Subaru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} said gave him a flash of insight, he said.{He said the thing Subaru-san told him let him figure it out. / 昴さんの　一言で\Nピーンと来たんだって。}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.89,0:14:45.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, you mean the message he asked me to tell Shin'ichi,\N{Hmm... he said I should tell Shin'ichiああ　新一に\N伝えてくれって言ってた→} "You're just like the shinobi, Kirigakure Saizō"?{"You're a ninja, like Saizōda Kirigakure", those were the words he told me to say. 「君はまるで忍...　霧隠才蔵だ」ってあの言葉ね。}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.02,0:14:49.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then do ninjas use bloody characters like this one a lot?{By any chance, is it that ninjas used to write characters in blood [like this one]?　ひょっとして→\N\Nこれって忍者が\Nよく使ってた血文字とか？}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.45,0:14:53.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not it. Kirigakure Saizō was one of the Sanada Ten Braves.{That's not it, Kirigakure Saizō was one of the Ten Heroes of Sanada. / 違うよ　霧隠才蔵は\N真田十勇士の一人。}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.78,0:14:57.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The war banner of the Sanada clan\Nhad six {\i1}mon{\i0} coins on it, right?{Have[n't] you heard about the Sanada House's six-cpin banner? / 真田家の旗印って言えば\N六文銭でしょ？}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.69,0:14:59.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's how I figured it out!{That's how I realized it! / だから　わかったんだ！}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.30,0:15:05.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This bloody character wasn't made by being written,{That this character written in blood wasn't drawn by hand, / この血文字は\N書いたんじゃなくて→} but instead a shape created from six round coins.{but by some arrangement of six [round objects, like] coins. / 六つの丸い小銭があったから\N出来た形だってね。}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.29,0:15:06.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh...?{へぇ～！}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.57,0:15:10.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah... O-Of course, that's what Shin'ichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-niichan{\r} said.{Uhh... o-of course Shin'ichi-niichan was the one who said that. / あっ　も　もちろん→\N\N新一兄ちゃんが\N言ってたんだよ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.30,0:15:14.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the case ten years ago was an accidental death, right?{Then, the incident from ten years ago was an accidental death? / でも　１０年前の事件は\N事故死でしょ？→}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.21,0:15:18.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The nursery principal stumbled on the stone paving in the park and fell,{The nursery principal stumbled on the cobblestone walkway of the park and fell down. / 保育園の園長が\N公園の石畳に躓いて転んで→}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.07,0:15:23.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,breaking the fishbowl he was carrying,{The fishbowl he was carrying at that time shattered, / その時　抱えてた\N金魚鉢が割れて→} which pierced his heart and ended up killing him.{and [a shard] got stuck in his chest, killing him, like it was written. / 胸に刺さって　亡くなったって\Nことになってるけど。}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.79,0:15:28.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,C-Could that have been a theft case too?{C-Could it also have been a case of theft there? / あっ　あれも\N実は窃盗事件だったってわけ？}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.39,0:15:31.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But in the photo of the scene from ten years ago,{But, in the picture of the scene taken ten years ago / でも　１０年前の現場写真には→}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.26,0:15:37.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,there were the flowers offered by the kid who discovered the corpse,{the first person who found the body, a kid, had gathered flowers from the park as an offering.遺体の第一発見者の子がお供えした→\N\N公園の花はあったけど} but nothing like a cigarette.{The was no such thing as a cigarette there.タバコなんてなかったよ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.83,0:15:42.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Shin'ichi never said that his wallet had been stolen either.{Besides, the purse wasn't taken from him [in the way / like] Shin'ichi just explained.それに　財布が盗られたなんて話新一　してなかったし。}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.31,0:15:45.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then was that case really a murder?{Then, could that case from ten years ago be a murder? / じゃあ　１０年前のは\Nやっぱり殺人？}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.50,0:15:48.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, that case was about the six {\i1}mon{\i0} too.{No, that case was related to the six-coin banner as well.いや　その事件こそ→\N\N六文銭だったんだよ。\Nえっ！？}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.59,0:15:57.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Remember, the boy who discovered the body, Ryōsuke Nishimura,{You see, the first one who found the body [was] that kid, Ryōsuke Nishimura.ホラ　第一発見者の\N西村亮佑って少年→} found the principal collapsed in the park, not moving.{The principal, [after] falling in the park, was unable to move.園長が\N公園で倒れて動かないのを→}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.31,0:16:03.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He thought that he was dead,{[Then] that kid saw [him], though he was dead,その子が見つけて\N亡くなったと思い→} so by the corpse, he left some flowers as an offering...{and left a flower offering next to his corpse.花と一緒に遺体のそばに\Nお供えしたのさ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.80,0:16:06.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the six {\i1}mon{\i0}-toll needed to cross the Sanzu River.{ Sanzu River is the Buddhist religion's equivalent of River Styx [And] the six coins required as toll for crossing the Sanzu River as well. / 三途の川の渡し賃である六文銭をね。}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.98,0:16:09.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-The Sanzu River?{Sanzu River, you say? / さ　三途の川って。}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.30,0:16:11.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wasn't he just five years old and at nursery?{Wasn't he [just] a five-year-old kindergartener? / ５歳の幼稚園児だよ？}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.43,0:16:14.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But he was a child from a temple, wasn't he?{But he was [a child from a temple], wasn't he? / でも　お寺の子だったんだろ？}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.09,0:16:16.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a chance that he could've heard about it from his parents, right?{Couldn't it have been that he heard it from his parents? / 親に聞かされてたってことも→\N\Nあるんじゃないか？}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.77,0:16:18.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...{あぁ...。}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.32,0:16:23.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If someone dies without having six {\i1}mon{\i0},{If a deceased person doesn't have the six coins required to pay / 亡くなった人に\N六文銭を持たせないと→} then at the shore of the Sanzu River,{their toll to Sanzu River's ferrywoman, Tatsueba, / 三途の川の畔にいる\N奪衣婆に→}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.92,0:16:28.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Datsueba takes their clothes instead,{she'd take all their clothes and finally / 衣服を剥ぎ取られて→} and they fall into Hell.{they would fall [down] [into / to] Hell. / 地獄に\N落ちてしまうってね。}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.10,0:16:35.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That boy had likely heard about that story,{Most likely, that kid had heard about that story, / 恐らく\Nその話を聞いていた少年は→} so he left an offering of six {\i1}mon{\i0} coins beside the principal's corpse.{so he left six coins next to the principal's corpse as an offering. / 園長の遺体のそばに六文銭を供えて→}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.30,0:16:39.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then to prevent them from being stolen,{And then, to prevent them from being stolen, / それを\N誰かに盗られないように→} he hid them by surrounding them with flowers.{花で囲って隠したんだ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.04,0:16:45.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,B-But even if he lived at a temple,{H-However, even if he was a [child from a temple], / で　でもさ\Nいくらお寺の子でも→} would he really be carrying around six old {\i1}mon{\i0} coins?{blu note: added old to reinforce to the viewer that mon is outdated currencywould he be carrying around six coins [he could use for that]? / 六文銭なんて\N持ち歩いてるかな？}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.44,0:16:49.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He didn't have them, so he used something else that looks similar instead.{Because he didn't have [any], he used something else to replace them. / 無かったから　よく似た\N別の物で代用したんだよ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.54,0:16:50.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something else?{別の物？}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.90,0:16:54.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know, what that kid was carrying in one of the photos.{See, that kid had it in one of the pictures that were taken, didn't he? / ホラ　その子が\N写真の中で持ってただろ？}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.43,0:16:59.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah! The ring-shaped candy!{Huh?! [The] ring-shaped candy! / あっ！？穴開きドロップ！！}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.28,0:17:06.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right! Instead of the six {\i1}mon{\i0} coins,{Instead of the six coins, he put that / そう！\Nそれを六文銭の代わりに→} he left six candies by the corpse's left hand,{next to the deceased's left hand / 遺体の左手のそばに置いて→} and hit them with flowers.{and [camouflaged / covered / hid] them with flowers. / 花で隠したけど}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.85,0:17:11.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the blood flowing from the corpse got in through the gap formed by his thumb,{Blood flowing from the body got there through the gap formed by his thumb, / 親指の関節の隙間から→\N遺体から\N流れ出た血が侵入し→}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.37,0:17:15.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and just by coincidence happened to create such a sinister bloody character.{and, due to that, the sinister character written in blood ended up [being formed / taking shape]. / 偶然にも　あんな不吉な血文字が\N出来てしまったってわけさ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.76,0:17:20.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why nobody noticed{That's why, until the body was moved,だから　遺体を動かすまで→} the bloody "death" character until the corpse was moved.{the "death" character written in blood remained unnoticed.「死」の血文字に\N気付かなかったんだよ。→}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.70,0:17:25.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before the corpse was moved, the bloody character was seen as an extension of his left hand.{Before the corpse was moved, the blood around its left hand had already dried up, forming the character written in blood 動かす前は　血文字が\N左手と一体化してたから→}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.34,0:17:27.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why there wasn't any blood under his left hand in the photo,{In the photo, there's no blood under the left hand,写真じゃ\N左手の下には血はないのに→}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.96,0:17:31.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,even though there was said to be some on his palm and fingers.{but it was said there was blood on the palm and fingers.手の平や指に\N血が付いてたって言うしね。}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.23,0:17:36.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that's it! That long, straight gap{I get it! So, instead of a cigarette, it was the deceased's thumbそっか！\N遺体の親指がタバコの代わりに→} wasn't made by a cigarette, but by the corpse's thumb!{what made that long and narrow gap!あの細長い隙間を作ったのね！}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.85,0:17:40.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There weren't any candies anywhere in the photo though...{However, the photograph showed no ring-shaped candies there...でも　写真にはドロップなんて写ってなかったけど...。}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.99,0:17:47.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The dog that boy'd been looking after in the park probably took them and ate them,{Most likely, the dog that kid had been keeping in the park ate them up.多分　その少年が公園で飼ってた\N犬が咥えて持ってったんだよ。} disturbing the flowers.{And disarranged the flowers [as well].花を蹴散らして。\Nえっ...？}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.62,0:17:55.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That dog didn't have a collar in the photo,{That dog was shown without a collar in the pictures,あの犬　写真じゃ\N首輪してなかったし→} and there were three of those candies in his bowl too.{and there were three [ring-shaped / of that kind of] candy in his food bowl.餌の皿に\Nドロップが三つ入ってたしな。}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.30,0:18:00.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then why didn't Shin'ichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s dad{だったら\Nなんで新一君のお父さんは→} announce what really happened publicly?{share the truth [about it]?その真相を\N世間に公表しなかったの？}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.83,0:18:05.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's because there was quite an uproar about that bloody character{Since that character written in blood was said to be the first [in a series of] bizarre murders,あの血文字で\N猟奇殺人の始まりだって→} sparking a chain of bizarre murders.{which had stirred up [quite] a commotion.騒ぎになってしまったからさ。\Nあっ...。}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.39,0:18:11.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Depending on how it was interpreted,{Depending on the interpretation,取りようによっては→} it could have been misunderstood as the kid playing an imprudent prank,{the kid could've been misunderstood as having done an imprudent prank,子供の不謹慎なイタズラだと\N誤解され→}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.47,0:18:15.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and if that was reported in the news, he could end up being ostracised.{which would've resulted in him receiving a [beating / bashing] if it were reported.それが報道されたら　少年が\Nバッシングを受けかねない。}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.99,0:18:19.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Couldn't that be the reason why he kept it quiet?{In that case, couldn't he have decided to not say anything?だから　あえて沈黙することに\Nしたってところかな？}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.36,0:18:26.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, judging by how{Well, by looking at this character written in bloodまぁ　今回の血文字を見て→} quickly Inspector Megure{and realizing there had to be [round] coins so quickly,すぐに\N丸い小銭があったことを→} figured out that there were round coins in the bloody character in this case,{it seemed as if Inspector Megure had already seen through what had really happened,目暮警部が\N見抜いたところを見ると→}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.12,0:18:30.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he probably told the Inspector what happened at least.{null.AR: We should probably add a mention to Yuusaku or the previous case here, since it's been a few lines since it was last mentioned, and it can no longer be used as a tacit objectso he was probably told the truth. / 警部には\N真相を話してたようだけど。}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.08,0:18:31.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wasn't just the Inspector.{He didn't tell just the Inspector. / 警部にだけじゃないよ。\Nえっ？}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.63,0:18:37.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Back then, Dad spoke with that kid{At that time, dad spoke with that kidあの時　父さん　その少年と話してたんだ} with a smile on his face.{　笑顔でね。}
